ores.espn.go.com/ncf/recap?gameId=262590084|title=Hill tosses 4 TDs as I-AA Salukis shock Indiana|date=September 16, 2006|accessdate=January 12, 2011}}</ref> becoming the first [[Missouri Valley Football Conference]] (MVFC) school to win against a [[Big Ten Conference]] member.{{cn|date=May 2019}} In 2007, the Salukis were victorious against [[Northern Illinois University]].  This marked the second consecutive year that SIU had beaten an [[NCAA Division I Football Bowl Subdivision|FBS]] program.<ref>{{cite web|website=[[ESPN]]|agency=[[Associated Press]]|url=http://espn.go.com/ncf/recap?gameId=272512459|title=S. Illinois 34, N. Illinois 31|date=September 8, 2007|accessdate=January 12, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2000s, SIU set then-MVFC records with 99 consecutive weeks ranked in the top-25 and 14-straight MVFC wins.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.daily-chronicle.com/articles/2007/09/08/sports/sports03.txt|title=SIU becoming powerhouse at I-AA level|author=|date=|website=daily-chronicle.com|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Conference affiliations==\n* Independent (1913\u20131924, 1962\u20131976)\n* [[Interstate Intercollegiate Athletic Conference]] (1925\u20131961) \n* [[Missouri Valley Conference]] (1977\u20131984)\n* [[Missouri Valley Football Conference]] (1985\u2013present) (known as the Gateway Football Conference until June 2008)\n\n== Postseason games ==\nThe Salukis have appeared in two [[bowl games]], compiling a 2\u20130 record.\n===Bowl games===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Southern Illinois Salukis|Season|Bowl|Opponent|Result}}\n|-\n| {{cfb link|year=1947|team=Southern Illinois Salukis|title=1947}} || Corn Bowl || [[North Central College|North Central]] || '''W''' 21\u20130\n|-\n| {{cfb link|year=1949|team=Southern Illinois Salukis|title=1949}} || [[Shrine Bowl]] || {{cfb link|year=1949|team=Indiana State Sycamores|title=Indiana State}} || '''W''' 21\u20130\n|}\n\n===Division I-AA/FCS playoffs===\nThe Salukis have appeared in 15