{"title_page": "East Meadow Union Free School District", "text_new": "'''East Meadow Union Free School District''' ('''EMUFSD''') is a school district headquartered in the Leon J. Campo Salisbury Center in [[Westbury, New York]].<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.emufsd.us/|title=Home|publisher=East Meadow Union Free School District|accessdate=2020-04-19|quote=The Leon J. Campo Salisbury Center 718 The Plain Road<nowiki> | Westbury, NY 11590</nowiki>}}</ref>\n\nThe district was first established as the '''Common School District #3''' in 1812, with a change in organization two years later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.emufsd.us/Assets/district_documents/030717_A_Short_History_of_East_Meadow_Schools.pdf?t=636244931036000000|title=A Short History of East Meadow Schools|publisher=East Meadow Union Free School District|accessdate=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==Schools==\n; High schools\n* [[W.T. Clarke High School]]\n* [[East Meadow High School]]\n\n; Middle schools\n* W.T. Clarke Middle School\n* Woodland Middle School\n\n; Elementary schools\n* Barnum Woods\n* Bowling Green School\n* George McVey Elementary School\n* Meadowbrook Elementary School\n* Parkway Elementary School\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.emufsd.us East Meadow Union Free School District]\n* {{webarchive|url=http://web.archive.org/*/http://www.eastmeadow.k12.ny.us/|title=East Meadow Union Free School District (eastmeadow.k12.ny.us)}}\n[[Category:School districts in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:1812 establishments in the United States]]\n{{NY-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''East Meadow Union Free School District''' ('''EMUFSD''') is a school district headquartered in the Leon J. Campo Salisbury Center in [[Westbury, New York]].<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.emufsd.us/|title=Home|publisher=East Meadow Union Free School District|accessdate=2020-04-19|quote=The Leon J. Campo Salisbury Center 718 The Plain Road | Westbury, NY 11590}}</ref>\n\nThe district was first established as the '''Common School District #3''' in 1812, with a change in organization two years later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.emufsd.us/Assets/district_documents/030717_A_Short_History_of_East_Meadow_Schools.pdf?t=636244931036000000|title=A Short History of East Meadow Schools|publisher=East Meadow Union Free School District|accessdate=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==Schools==\n; High schools\n* [[W.T. Clarke High School]]\n* [[East Meadow High School]]\n\n; Middle schools\n* W.T. Clarke Middle School\n* Woodland Middle School\n\n; Elementary schools\n* Barnum Woods\n* Bowling Green School\n* George McVey Elementary School\n* Meadowbrook Elementary School\n* Parkway Elementary School\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.emufsd.us East Meadow Union Free School District]\n* {{webarchive|url=http://web.archive.org/*/http://www.eastmeadow.k12.ny.us/|title=East Meadow Union Free School District (eastmeadow.k12.ny.us)}}\n[[Category:School districts in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:1812 establishments in the United States]]\n{{NY-school-stub}}\n", "name_user": "WhisperToMe", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Meadow_Union_Free_School_District"}
{"title_page": "No Min-woo", "text_new": "{{distinguish|text=[[Boyfriend (band)|Boyfriend's]] No Min-woo}}\n{{short description|South Korean actor and singer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Korean name|No}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = No Min-woo\n| image       = No Minwoo, Partners for Justice 2.jpg\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1986|05|29}}\n| birth_place = [[Japan]]<ref name=\"Interj\u00fa\">{{cite web|url=http://lady.khan.co.kr/khlady.html?mode=view&code=5&artid=201002041510511|title=\ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 '\ud30c\uc2a4\ud0c0'\uc758 \uaf43\ubbf8\ub0a8 \uc170\ud504 \ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0|work=[[Kyunghyang Shinmun]]|date=February 4, 2010|accessdate=2012-12-25}}</ref>\n|occupation   = Actor, singer, dancer\n|years_active = 2004\u2013present\n|agent        = MJ Dreamys\n| module      = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background  =solo_singer\n|instrument   = Piano, guitar, drums, saxophone<ref name=\"seoulj\" />\n| alias       = ICON<br>MINUE\n|years_active = 2004\u2013present \n|associated_acts = [[TraxX]], 24/7\n|label        = {{hlist|[[SM Entertainment|SM]]|[[Core Contents Media]]|MJ Dreamsys}}\n| module      = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes|color=transparent\n| hangul      = {{linktext|\ub178|\ubbfc\uc6b0}}\n| hanja       = {{linktext|\u9b6f|\u654f|\u5b87}}\n| rr          = No Min-u\n| mr          = No Min-u\n\n}}\n}}\n}}\n'''No Min-woo''' ({{ko-hhrm|\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0}}; born May 29, 1986) is a South Korean actor and musician. He is also known under the stage names ICON and MINUE. He debuted as a drummer in [[TRAX (band)|TRAX]] in 2004, and left the band two years later. In 2008, he began acting in various television series and movies, such as ''[[Pasta (TV series)|Pasta]]'', ''[[My Girlfriend is a Nine-Tailed Fox]]'' and ''[[Full House Take 2]]'', and he regularly contributes to movie and drama soundtracks. In 2013, No made a comeback as a singer under the stage name ICON. In 2016 he enlisted in the military, and returned in 2018.\n\n==Career==\n[[File:140210-\uc5f0\uc560\uc9d5\ud06c\uc2a4-vip\uc2dc\uc0ac\ud68c\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0.jpg|thumb|No Min-woo in 2014]]\nNo Min-woo was born in Japan while his mother, then 20 years old, was aspiring to become an [[enka]] singer there.<ref name=\"Interj\u00fa\" /> He was moving back and forth between Korea and Japan for a long time, and started playing the piano at age 7.<ref name=\"seoulj\">{{cite web|url=http://seouljournal.com/entertainment/item/219-no-min-woo.html|title=A Musical and Movie ICON|publisher=Seoul Journal|accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref> He has a younger brother, Jeong-hun, who is a singer under the pseudonym [[I'll (singer)|I'll]] (\uc544\uc77c).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hankyung.com/entertainment/article/201907300608H|title=\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0 \"\ub3d9\uc0dd \uc544\uc77c, \uc9c0\uae08\ucc98\ub7fc \uacb8\uc190\ud558\uac8c \ucb49 \uac00\uae38\" \uc751\uc6d0 \uc804\ud574|date=2019-07-30|accessdate=2019-07-30|publisher=\ud55c\uad6d\uacbd\uc81c\uc2e0\ubb38|language=Korean}}</ref>\n\nHe made his debut as the drummer (with the stage name Rose) in the rock band [[The TRAX ]]in 2004.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hong|first=Lucia|title=No Min-woo to celebrate 27th birthday with fans in Seoul|url=http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012051418245078141|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=10Asia|date=May 14, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425044422/http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012051418245078141|archive-date=April 25, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Prior to debut, No Min-woo appeared in \"2002 Survival Audition [[Moon Hee Jun|HeeJun]] vs. [[KangTa]] Battle of the Century\" with bandmates Typhoon and Attack, as well as [[Xiah Junsu]] , [[Super Junior]]'s [[Sungmin]] and [[Eunhyuk]]. No Minwoo left TRAX in 2006, and briefly became a guitarist for The Romantist before it disbanded. In 2009 he returned to the music scene as the leader of the project group 24/7, with [[Lee Jang-woo]] and [[Hyun Woo]]. They released the single ''24 Hours a Day, 7 Days a Week''.\n\nMin-woo began pursuing an acting career in 2008, and gained notice with his supporting roles in the 2010 TV series ''[[Pasta (TV series)|Pasta]]'' and ''[[My Girlfriend is a Nine-Tailed Fox]]''. He landed his first leading role in the four-episode [[Drama City|drama special]] ''Rock Rock Rock'', a biographical film about the life of [[Boohwal]] lead guitarist [[Kim Tae-won]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010122419474730900|script-title=ko:'\ub77d\ub77d\ub77d' \ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, \ubd80\ud65c \uacf5\uc5f0\uc11c \uae40\ud0dc\uc6d0\uacfc \ud568\uaed8 \ub178\ub798\ud55c\ub2e4|work=Asiae|language=Korean|accessdate=2012-12-11|date=December 24, 2012}}</ref> Then for his role as a cancer patient in 2011's ''[[Midas (TV series)|Midas]]'', No lost 9.5 kilograms (21 pounds).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/04/no-min-woo-lost-9-5kg-for-midas|title=No Min Woo lost 9.5&nbsp;kg for ''Midas''|date=April 1, 2011|work=[[Allkpop]]|accessdate=2012-12-11}}</ref> His long-delayed drama ''[[Full House Take 2]]'' (a loose sequel to the [[Full House (2004 TV series)|2004 hit]]) secured air dates on Japan's [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]] and Korean cable channel [[SBS Plus]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ho|first=Stewart|title=''Full House Take 2'' Starring Park Ki Woong, Hwang Jung Eum, Noh Min Woo Premieres on SBS Plus on Oct 22|url=http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=16976|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=enewsWorld|date=October 9, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130123225217/http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=16976|archive-date=January 23, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Hye-ji|title=No Min-woo \"I Looked Like Grandpa When Dancing\"|url=http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012101910050920935|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=10Asia|date=October 19, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215830/http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012101910050920935|archive-date=October 4, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> No was cast as the male lead in the Chinese TV series ''Love Expiration Date'', for which he will also serve as OST music director, composing and writing songs for the soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ho|first=Stewart|title=Noh Min Woo Cast in Chinese Drama, Will Direct the Drama's OST|url=http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=8327|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130129053221/http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=8327|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 29, 2013|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=enewsWorld|date=June 21, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Suk|first=Monica|title=No Min-woo to play male lead in Chinese TV series with Li Qin|url=http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012062117445960769|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=10Asia|date=June 21, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215408/http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012062117445960769|archive-date=October 4, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Tae-ho|title=Actor No Min-woo to Debut as Music Director with Soundtrack to Chinese Drama|url=http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012101115535411822|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=10Asia|date=October 11, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215537/http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012101115535411822|archive-date=October 4, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012 his contract with [[Core Contents Media]] came to an end, and he established his own management company, MJ Dreamsys.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20121207n25071|script-title=ko:\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, 1\uc778 \uae30\ud68d\uc0ac \uc124\ub9bd\u2026\ud55c\u00b7\uc77c\uc11c \ub2e8\ub3c5\ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \uac1c\ucd5c|work=[[Nate (web portal)|Nate]]|language=Korean|date=December 7, 2012|accessdate=2012-12-09}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, on July 1, No released his MV, ''ROCKSTAR'', under his newly opened YouTube channel, officialminewTV.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BRYHzR-7dLQ|title=ICON \u2013 ROCKSTAR [OFFICIAL VIDEO]|language=Korean|accessdate=2013-07-01|date=July 1, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, No appeared in a minor role in ''[[Roaring Currents]]'' (released July 30, 2014),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.joins.com/article/15481883|title='\uba85\ub7c9'\uc774 \uc5ec\ub7ff \uc0b4\ub838\ub2e4\u2026 \ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0 \uc5f0\uae30 \uc7ac\uc870\uba85|date=2014-08-08|accessdate=2019-08-09|publisher=Jungang Ilbo|language=ko}}</ref> which became the highest-grossing film of all time in South Korea. Later in 2014, No played one of the main characters in ''[[The Greatest Marriage]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mnetamerica.com/news/article/70182/no-min-woo-confirmed-for-greatest-marriage|title=No Min Woo to Play a Rich Boy in \u2032Greatest Marriage\u2032|date=2014-07-07|accessdate=2019-08-09|publisher=Mnet America|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190809120757/http://www.mnetamerica.com/news/article/70182/no-min-woo-confirmed-for-greatest-marriage|archive-date=August 9, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nNo starred in [[MBC Plus Media|MBC Dramanet]]'s ''[[My Unfortunate Boyfriend]]'', which premiered on April 10, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dramafever.com/news/no-min-woo-already-has-his-next-drama-lined-up/|publisher=Drama Fever|accessdate=December 13, 2014|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20141213074804/http://www.dramafever.com/news/no-min-woo-already-has-his-next-drama-lined-up/|archivedate=2014-12-13|title=No Min Woo already has his next drama lined up}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, No confirmed to star in the lead role of [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] drama ''[[Partners for Justice 2]]'' as a doctor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2019040409184906920|title='\uac80\ubc95\ub0a8\ub140 \uc2dc\uc98c2' \ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0X\uac15\uc2b9\ud604 \ucd9c\uc5f0..\u65b0 \uc5bc\uad74(\uacf5\uc2dd)|publisher=Star News|date=April 4, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n===Lawsuit===\nIn April 2015, No filed a lawsuit against his former agency, [[S.M. Entertainment]], as well as reported the agency to the [[Fair Trade Commission (South Korea)|South Korea Fair Trade Commission]]. Documents from the lawsuit reveal that No originally signed a 17-year exclusive contract with [[S.M. Entertainment|S.M]]. No sought 100 million KRW for damages resulting from the agency's interference in his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.hankyung.com/article/2015051187077|title=\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, SM\uc5d4\ud130 \uc0c1\ub300 \uc18c\uc1a1\uc81c\uae30\u2026\"JYJ\ucc98\ub7fc 17\ub144 \ub178\uc608\uacc4\uc57d\" \ucda9\uaca9|language=ko|date=May 11, 2015|website=Hankyung}}</ref> \nOn 21 July 2016 No lost his damage suit against [[S.M. Entertainment|S.M]] as a result of insufficient evidence court ruled out the contract between [[S.M. Entertainment|S.M]] and No invalid.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://view.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2016072109260925688|title=\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, SM \uc0c1\ub300 1\uc5b5\uc6d0 \uc190\ubc30\uc18c \ud328\uc18c\u2026\ubc95\uc6d0 \u201c \ub9e4\ub2c8\uc9c0\uba3c\ud2b8 \uc18c\ud640 \uadfc\uac70 \uc5c6\uc5b4\u201d|language=ko|date=21 July 2016|website=Asiae}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, it was reported No had lost the appeal in his lawsuit against [[S.M. Entertainment]] due to the insufficient evidence to the above stated claims.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.nate.com/view/20180620n26427|title=SM \uc0c1\ub300\ub85c \ub300\ubc95\uc6d0 \uac04 \ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, \uacb0\uad6d \ud328\uc18c \ud655\uc815|language=ko|date=20 June 2018|website=Nate}}</ref>\n\n===Military enlistment===\nNo was confirmed to have quietly enlisted for his [[Conscription in South Korea|mandatory military service]] in October 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mydaily.co.kr/new_yk/html/read.php?newsid=201612061501581138&ext=na|script-title=ko:\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0 \uce21 \"10\uc6d4\ub9d0 \ud604\uc5ed \uc785\ub300, \uad70\uc0dd\ud65c \uc911\uc774\ub2e4\" \uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5|language=ko|date=6 December 2016|website=My Daily}}</ref> He was discharged in July 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201804051056122410|title=\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0 7\uc6d4 \uc81c\ub300 \uc55e\ub46c \u201c\ubcf5\uadc0\uc640 \ud568\uaed8 \ud65c\ub3d9 \uc608\uc815\u201d|publisher=Newsen|language=Korean|date=2018-04-05|accessdate=2019-08-09}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n===Television drama===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:650px\"\n|-\n! width=10|Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''Propose''\n| \n| [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Truth''\n| \n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Detective Mr. Lee''\n| \n| [[tvN]]\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2009\n| ''Tae-hee, Hye-kyo, Ji-hyun''\n| Noh Min Woo\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n|-\n| ''Mrs. Town''\n| Jackie Jung's younger lover\n| [[tvN]]\n|-\n| ''Jung Yak-yong''\n| [[cameo appearance|cameo]]\n| [[Orion Cinema Network|OCN]]\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2010\n| ''[[Pasta (TV series)|Pasta]]''\n| Philip\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n|-\n| ''[[My Girlfriend is a Nine-Tailed Fox]]''\n| Park Dong-joo\n| [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]\n|-\n| ''[[Rock, Rock, Rock (TV series)|Rock, Rock, Rock]]''\n| Kim Tae-won\n| [[KBS2]]\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Midas (TV series)|Midas]]''\n| Yoo Myung-joon\n| [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Full House Take 2]]''\n| Lee Tae-ik\n| [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]]/[[SBS Plus]]\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2013\n| ''[[Monstar (TV series)|Monstar]]''\n| Daniel Park ([[cameo appearance|cameo]],ep12)\n| [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]\n|-\n| ''Love Expiration Date''\n| Lee Ti En\n| ZJSTV\n|-\n| ''[[The Blade and Petal]]''\n| [[Yeon Namsaeng]]\n| [[KBS2]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2014\n| ''[[God's Gift - 14 Days]]''\n| Theo\n| [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]\n|-\n| ''[[The Greatest Marriage]]''\n| Park Tae-yeon\n| TV Chosun\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2015\n| ''[[My Unfortunate Boyfriend]]''\n| Yoon Tae-woon\n| [[MBC Plus Media|MBC Dramanet]]\n|-\n| ''Eating Existence'' (2015)\n| Park Byeong\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Partners for Justice 2]]''\n| Dr. Jang Chul / Dr. K\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n|}\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:650px\"\n|-\n! width=10|Year\n! Title\n! Role\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2008\n| ''[[Story of Wine]]''\n| Taek-jin\n|-\n| ''[[A Frozen Flower]]''\n| Min-woo\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''Ghastly''\n| Cheol-Woong\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2014\n| ''One Day, First Love Invaded Me''\n| Min-Hyuk\n|-\n| ''[[The Admiral: Roaring Currents]]''\n| Haru\n|-\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n{{see also|The TRAX}}\n* ''[[Partners for Justice]] 2'' OST (2019)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/ko-kr/entertainment/music/%EB%85%B8%EB%AF%BC%EC%9A%B0-%EA%B2%80%EB%B2%95%EB%82%A8%EB%85%802-ost-drk-%EB%B0%9C%ED%91%9C%EC%83%A4%EC%9A%B0%ED%8C%85%EC%9C%BC%EB%A1%9C-%EB%85%B9%EC%9D%B8-%EB%8B%A5%ED%84%B0k/ar-AADLUs9|title=\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, '\uac80\ubc95\ub0a8\ub1402' OST 'Dr.K' \ubc1c\ud45c...\uc0e4\uc6b0\ud305\uc73c\ub85c \ub179\uc778 \ub2e5\ud130K|publisher=OSEN|accessdate=2019-08-09|language=Korean|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190809114552/https://www.msn.com/ko-kr/entertainment/music/%25EB%2585%25B8%25EB%25AF%25BC%25EC%259A%25B0-%25EA%25B2%2580%25EB%25B2%2595%25EB%2582%25A8%25EB%2585%25802-ost-drk-%25EB%25B0%259C%25ED%2591%259C%25EC%2583%25A4%25EC%259A%25B0%25ED%258C%2585%25EC%259C%25BC%25EB%25A1%259C-%25EB%2585%25B9%25EC%259D%25B8-%25EB%258B%25A5%25ED%2584%25B0k/ar-AADLUs9|archive-date=August 9, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n** ''Dr.K''\n* ''Gravity'' (Japanese, as ''Minue'', 2016)\n** Gravity\n** We rock\n** believe\n* ''[[My Unfortunate Boyfriend]] ''OST (2015)\n** I Love You\n** Shining Love\n* ''ICON''  the 1st Single Album (2013)\n** ROCKSTAR\n** Baby\n** Hello\n** Alive\n* [[The Greatest Marriage]]'' ''OST (2014)\n** Crazy Love\n* ''[[God's Gift - 14 Days]]'' OST (2014)\n** Snake Eyes\n** Heaven\n* Love Expiration Date'' ''OST (2013)\n** 1 Minute 1 Second\n* ''[[Full House Take 2]]'' OST (2012)\n** Touch (singer)\n** Sad Touch (singer)\n** Hello Hello (singer)\n* ''[[Midas]]'' OST (2011)\n** \uc2ac\ud508\uc0ac\ub791 Seulpheun Sarang (lyricist, singer)\n** \uc0ac\ub791\ud574\ub3c4 \ub418\ub098\uc694 Sarangaedo doinayo (composer, singer)\n*  ''[[My Girlfriend is a Nine-Tailed Fox]]'' OST (2010)\n** Trap\n* ''[[Story of Wine]]'' OST (lyricist, music director, singer; 2009)\n** \uc790\uc791\ub098\ubb34 (Love is you)\u3000\u3000\n** Even now (Singer:Sunny)\u3000\u3000\n** Firstsnow\u3000\u3000\n** Nobody\u3000\u3000\n** Confession\n** MyPerfect Romance\u3000\u3000\n** Peaceof Melody\u3000\u3000\n** Express\n* That guy's woman (2009)\n* ''[[Rhapsody (Trax album)|Rhapsody]]'' Album (2005)\n* Blaze Away Album (2005)\n* ''[[Paradox]] ''Album (2004)\n* [[Scorpio (Trax song)|Scorpio]] Album{{citation needed|date=May 2014}} (2004)\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2010\n| [[2010 KBS Drama Awards|KBS Drama Awards]]\n| Best Actor in a One-Act/Special/Short Drama\n| ''[[Rock, Rock, Rock (TV series)|Rock, Rock, Rock]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[2010 SBS Drama Awards|SBS Drama Awards]]\n| New Star Award\n| ''[[My Girlfriend Is a Nine-Tailed Fox]]''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2019\n|World Star Entertainment\nAwards 2019\n|Hallyu Global Award 2019\n( Korean Wave Global Award)\n|\n|{{Won}}\n|<ref> {{https:// Namu.wiki/\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0-\ub098\ubb34\uc704\ud0a4 }} \nhttps://www.mjdreamsys.co.kr/MINUE Artist  </ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2|[[2019 MBC Drama Awards|MBC Drama Awards]]\n| Scene Stealer Award\n| rowspan=2|''[[Partners for Justice 2]]''\n| {{won}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1374425wpp/winners-of-the-2019-mbc-drama-awards|title=Winners Of The 2019 MBC Drama Awards|date=2019-12-30|website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2019-12-31}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2019\n|Best Couple Award <small>with [[Jung Jae-young]]</small>\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|No Min-woo}}\n* [http://mjdreamsys.co.kr/html/dh/artist/2 Official Website]\n* {{Instagram|icon_stagram}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:No, Min-woo}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:K-pop singers]]\n[[Category:Inha University alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:South Korean male singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean pop singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male television actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean television personalities]]\n[[Category:South Korean male film actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n[[Category:King of Mask Singer contestants]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|text=[[Boyfriend (band)|Boyfriend's]] No Min-woo}}\n{{short description|South Korean actor and singer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{Korean name|No}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = No Min-woo\n| image       = No Minwoo, Partners for Justice 2.jpg\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1986|05|29}}\n| birth_place = [[Japan]]<ref name=\"Interj\u00fa\">{{cite web|url=http://lady.khan.co.kr/khlady.html?mode=view&code=5&artid=201002041510511|title=\ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 '\ud30c\uc2a4\ud0c0'\uc758 \uaf43\ubbf8\ub0a8 \uc170\ud504 \ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0|work=[[Kyunghyang Shinmun]]|date=February 4, 2010|accessdate=2012-12-25}}</ref>\n|occupation  = Actor, singer, dancer\n|years_active    = 2004\u2013present\n|agent        = MJ Dreamys\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background=solo_singer\n|instrument      = Piano, guitar, drums, saxophone<ref name=\"seoulj\" />\n| alias            = ICON<br>MINUE\n|years_active    = 2004\u2013present \n|associated_acts     = [[TraxX]], 24/7\n|label        = {{hlist|[[SM Entertainment|SM]]|[[Core Contents Media]]|MJ Dreamsys}}\n| module      = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes|color=transparent\n| hangul      = {{linktext|\ub178|\ubbfc\uc6b0}}\n| hanja       = {{linktext|\u9b6f|\u654f|\u5b87}}\n| rr          = No Min-u\n| mr          = No Min-u\n\n}}\n}}\n}}\n'''No Min-woo''' ({{ko-hhrm|\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0}}; born May 29, 1986) is a South Korean actor and musician. He is also known under the stage names ICON and MINUE. He debuted as a drummer in [[TRAX (band)|TRAX]] in 2004, and left the band two years later. In 2008, he began acting in various television series and movies, such as ''[[Pasta (TV series)|Pasta]]'', ''[[My Girlfriend is a Nine-Tailed Fox]]'' and ''[[Full House Take 2]]'', and he regularly contributes to movie and drama soundtracks. In 2013, No made a comeback as a singer under the stage name ICON. In 2016 he enlisted in the military, and returned in 2018.\n\n==Career==\n[[File:140210-\uc5f0\uc560\uc9d5\ud06c\uc2a4-vip\uc2dc\uc0ac\ud68c\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0.jpg|thumb|No Min-woo in 2014]]\nNo Min-woo was born in Japan while his mother, then 20 years old, was aspiring to become an [[enka]] singer there.<ref name=\"Interj\u00fa\" /> He was moving back and forth between Korea and Japan for a long time, and started playing the piano at age 7.<ref name=\"seoulj\">{{cite web|url=http://seouljournal.com/entertainment/item/219-no-min-woo.html|title=A Musical and Movie ICON|publisher=Seoul Journal|accessdate=2017-04-03}}</ref> He has a younger brother, Jeong-hun, who is a singer under the pseudonym [[I'll (singer)|I'll]] (\uc544\uc77c).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hankyung.com/entertainment/article/201907300608H|title=\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0 \"\ub3d9\uc0dd \uc544\uc77c, \uc9c0\uae08\ucc98\ub7fc \uacb8\uc190\ud558\uac8c \ucb49 \uac00\uae38\" \uc751\uc6d0 \uc804\ud574|date=2019-07-30|accessdate=2019-07-30|publisher=\ud55c\uad6d\uacbd\uc81c\uc2e0\ubb38|language=Korean}}</ref>\n\nHe made his debut as the drummer (with the stage name Rose) in the rock band [[The TRAX ]]in 2004.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hong|first=Lucia|title=No Min-woo to celebrate 27th birthday with fans in Seoul|url=http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012051418245078141|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=10Asia|date=May 14, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425044422/http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012051418245078141|archive-date=April 25, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Prior to debut, No Min-woo appeared in \"2002 Survival Audition [[Moon Hee Jun|HeeJun]] vs. [[KangTa]] Battle of the Century\" with bandmates Typhoon and Attack, as well as [[Xiah Junsu]] , [[Super Junior]]'s [[Sungmin]] and [[Eunhyuk]]. No Minwoo left TRAX in 2006, and briefly became a guitarist for The Romantist before it disbanded. In 2009 he returned to the music scene as the leader of the project group 24/7, with [[Lee Jang-woo]] and [[Hyun Woo]]. They released the single ''24 Hours a Day, 7 Days a Week''.\n\nMin-woo began pursuing an acting career in 2008, and gained notice with his supporting roles in the 2010 TV series ''[[Pasta (TV series)|Pasta]]'' and ''[[My Girlfriend is a Nine-Tailed Fox]]''. He landed his first leading role in the four-episode [[Drama City|drama special]] ''Rock Rock Rock'', a biographical film about the life of [[Boohwal]] lead guitarist [[Kim Tae-won]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010122419474730900|script-title=ko:'\ub77d\ub77d\ub77d' \ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, \ubd80\ud65c \uacf5\uc5f0\uc11c \uae40\ud0dc\uc6d0\uacfc \ud568\uaed8 \ub178\ub798\ud55c\ub2e4|work=Asiae|language=Korean|accessdate=2012-12-11|date=December 24, 2012}}</ref> Then for his role as a cancer patient in 2011's ''[[Midas (TV series)|Midas]]'', No lost 9.5 kilograms (21 pounds).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/04/no-min-woo-lost-9-5kg-for-midas|title=No Min Woo lost 9.5&nbsp;kg for ''Midas''|date=April 1, 2011|work=[[Allkpop]]|accessdate=2012-12-11}}</ref> His long-delayed drama ''[[Full House Take 2]]'' (a loose sequel to the [[Full House (2004 TV series)|2004 hit]]) secured air dates on Japan's [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]] and Korean cable channel [[SBS Plus]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ho|first=Stewart|title=''Full House Take 2'' Starring Park Ki Woong, Hwang Jung Eum, Noh Min Woo Premieres on SBS Plus on Oct 22|url=http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=16976|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=enewsWorld|date=October 9, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130123225217/http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=16976|archive-date=January 23, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Hye-ji|title=No Min-woo \"I Looked Like Grandpa When Dancing\"|url=http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012101910050920935|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=10Asia|date=October 19, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215830/http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012101910050920935|archive-date=October 4, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> No was cast as the male lead in the Chinese TV series ''Love Expiration Date'', for which he will also serve as OST music director, composing and writing songs for the soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ho|first=Stewart|title=Noh Min Woo Cast in Chinese Drama, Will Direct the Drama's OST|url=http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=8327|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130129053221/http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=8327|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 29, 2013|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=enewsWorld|date=June 21, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Suk|first=Monica|title=No Min-woo to play male lead in Chinese TV series with Li Qin|url=http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012062117445960769|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=10Asia|date=June 21, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215408/http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012062117445960769|archive-date=October 4, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Tae-ho|title=Actor No Min-woo to Debut as Music Director with Soundtrack to Chinese Drama|url=http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012101115535411822|accessdate=2012-11-18|work=10Asia|date=October 11, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215537/http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2012101115535411822|archive-date=October 4, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012 his contract with [[Core Contents Media]] came to an end, and he established his own management company, MJ Dreamsys.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20121207n25071|script-title=ko:\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, 1\uc778 \uae30\ud68d\uc0ac \uc124\ub9bd\u2026\ud55c\u00b7\uc77c\uc11c \ub2e8\ub3c5\ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \uac1c\ucd5c|work=[[Nate (web portal)|Nate]]|language=Korean|date=December 7, 2012|accessdate=2012-12-09}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, on July 1, No released his MV, ''ROCKSTAR'', under his newly opened YouTube channel, officialminewTV.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BRYHzR-7dLQ|title=ICON \u2013 ROCKSTAR [OFFICIAL VIDEO]|language=Korean|accessdate=2013-07-01|date=July 1, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, No appeared in a minor role in ''[[Roaring Currents]]'' (released July 30, 2014),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.joins.com/article/15481883|title='\uba85\ub7c9'\uc774 \uc5ec\ub7ff \uc0b4\ub838\ub2e4\u2026 \ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0 \uc5f0\uae30 \uc7ac\uc870\uba85|date=2014-08-08|accessdate=2019-08-09|publisher=Jungang Ilbo|language=ko}}</ref> which became the highest-grossing film of all time in South Korea. Later in 2014, No played one of the main characters in ''[[The Greatest Marriage]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mnetamerica.com/news/article/70182/no-min-woo-confirmed-for-greatest-marriage|title=No Min Woo to Play a Rich Boy in \u2032Greatest Marriage\u2032|date=2014-07-07|accessdate=2019-08-09|publisher=Mnet America|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190809120757/http://www.mnetamerica.com/news/article/70182/no-min-woo-confirmed-for-greatest-marriage|archive-date=August 9, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nNo starred in [[MBC Plus Media|MBC Dramanet]]'s ''[[My Unfortunate Boyfriend]]'', which premiered on April 10, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dramafever.com/news/no-min-woo-already-has-his-next-drama-lined-up/|publisher=Drama Fever|accessdate=December 13, 2014|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20141213074804/http://www.dramafever.com/news/no-min-woo-already-has-his-next-drama-lined-up/|archivedate=2014-12-13|title=No Min Woo already has his next drama lined up}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, No confirmed to star in the lead role of [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] drama ''[[Partners for Justice 2]]'' as a doctor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2019040409184906920|title='\uac80\ubc95\ub0a8\ub140 \uc2dc\uc98c2' \ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0X\uac15\uc2b9\ud604 \ucd9c\uc5f0..\u65b0 \uc5bc\uad74(\uacf5\uc2dd)|publisher=Star News|date=April 4, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n===Lawsuit===\nIn April 2015, No filed a lawsuit against his former agency, [[S.M. Entertainment]], as well as reported the agency to the [[Fair Trade Commission (South Korea)|South Korea Fair Trade Commission]]. Documents from the lawsuit reveal that No originally signed a 17-year exclusive contract with [[S.M. Entertainment|S.M]]. No sought 100 million KRW for damages resulting from the agency's interference in his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.hankyung.com/article/2015051187077|title=\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, SM\uc5d4\ud130 \uc0c1\ub300 \uc18c\uc1a1\uc81c\uae30\u2026\"JYJ\ucc98\ub7fc 17\ub144 \ub178\uc608\uacc4\uc57d\" \ucda9\uaca9|language=ko|date=May 11, 2015|website=Hankyung}}</ref> \nOn 21 July 2016 No lost his damage suit against [[S.M. Entertainment|S.M]] as a result of insufficient evidence court ruled out the contract between [[S.M. Entertainment|S.M]] and No invalid.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://view.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2016072109260925688|title=\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, SM \uc0c1\ub300 1\uc5b5\uc6d0 \uc190\ubc30\uc18c \ud328\uc18c\u2026\ubc95\uc6d0 \u201c \ub9e4\ub2c8\uc9c0\uba3c\ud2b8 \uc18c\ud640 \uadfc\uac70 \uc5c6\uc5b4\u201d|language=ko|date=21 July 2016|website=Asiae}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, it was reported No had lost the appeal in his lawsuit against [[S.M. Entertainment]] due to the insufficient evidence to the above stated claims.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.nate.com/view/20180620n26427|title=SM \uc0c1\ub300\ub85c \ub300\ubc95\uc6d0 \uac04 \ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0, \uacb0\uad6d \ud328\uc18c \ud655\uc815|language=ko|date=20 June 2018|website=Nate}}</ref>\n\n===Military enlistment===\nNo was confirmed to have quietly enlisted for his [[Conscription in South Korea|mandatory military service]] in October 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mydaily.co.kr/new_yk/html/read.php?newsid=201612061501581138&ext=na|script-title=ko:\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0 \uce21 \"10\uc6d4\ub9d0 \ud604\uc5ed \uc785\ub300, \uad70\uc0dd\ud65c \uc911\uc774\ub2e4\" \uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5|language=ko|date=6 December 2016|website=My Daily}}</ref> He was discharged in July 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201804051056122410|title=\ub178\ubbfc\uc6b0 7\uc6d4 \uc81c\ub300 \uc55e\ub46c \u201c\ubcf5\uadc0\uc640 \ud568\uaed8 \ud65c\ub3d9 \uc608\uc815\u201d|publisher=Newsen|language=Korean|date=2018-04-05|accessdate=2019-08-09}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n===Television drama===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:650px\"\n|-\n! width=10|Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''Propose''\n| \n| [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Truth''\n| \n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Detective Mr. Lee''\n| \n| [[tvN]]\n|-\n| rowspan=3|2009\n| ''Tae-hee, Hye-kyo, Ji-hyun''\n| Noh Min Woo\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n|-\n| ''Mrs. Town''\n| Jackie Jung's younger lover\n| [[tvN]]\n|-\n| ''Jung Yak-yong''\n| [[cameo appearance|cameo]]\n| [[Orion Cinema Network|OCN]]\n|-\n| 